  ],
  "governance_notes": "All children are pure functions or atomic operations with no global variables. Data operations are limited to the three available stores (orders, inventory, payments). Each child's data operations are a subset of the parent's needs. ParseCommand and FormatResponse are stateless pure functions with no data store access. PlaceOrder and CancelOrder are atomic operations requiring write access to multiple stores. TrackOrder is a read-only pure function. The union of all children's data operations covers all parent data needs across the three stores."
}